arm-js
------

It emulates ARMv7 and some peripherals of Vesertile Express.
It can run Linux 3.3.8 and some user processes.

Get started
-----------

1. Prepare term.js
  1. Install js-beautify https://github.com/einars/js-beautify
  2. Run prepare_termjs.sh
2. Launch Chrome Web browser with special arguments (optional)
  1. If you run arm-js files on local filesystem, you need to run
     Chrome with --allow-file-access-from-files
  2. If you are using old Chrome, you may need --unlimited-quota-for-files
     to allow arm-js to store an emulator snaphost to local storage
  3. For example, for Mac OS X, execute
     'open -a "Google Chrome" --args --allow-file-access-from-files'
     on a terminal
3. Enjoy arm-js!
